          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUJ_vyqwAsGdAVVg0eIjtK7nJT6Z3MXzHr8hVSxwoodBsqR5OO5A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "I had been feeling under the weather for about 10 days so I made an appointment at CityMD to try to figure out what was going on.\n\nThe facility itself feels new and very clean and everyone I interacted with was pleasant, but ultimately, there was a massive miscommunication with my care. I was tested for Covid, Flu, Strep A and Mono and the doctor told me everything came back negative. He prescribed me a Medrol Dosepak (which wasn\u2019t really relevant to my situation and has many potential side effects) and suggested that if I don\u2019t feel better in a few days, I should be tested for Lupus or thyroid issues. I found this a little bizarre because I don\u2019t have any relevant past medical history and none of my annual blood tests have ever come back abnormal.\n\nThe following day, I signed into my portal to find that my Strep A result actually read \u201cPositive\u201d. CityMD apologized and called in an antibiotic to my pharmacy. On the way to pick up the antibiotic, I realized it was unclear whether the doctor told me the wrong result or whether the result was incorrectly entered into my profile. I called CityMD back and they basically said the fastest solution was to come back in and get re-tested. I confirmed the time I would be back in with the manager, but once I arrived, I found that he had apparently stepped out to lunch.\n\nOnce I was seen again, the second doctor confirmed that I was indeed positive for Strep A, but did not agree with the dose of the antibiotic that was sent in for me. I don\u2019t know what\u2019s going on at this facility, but this experience was a complete mess and I\u2019m not confident in the care that they are providing here. The way the manager handled this mistake was very disappointing as well.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT25sbmQySTBUR0ZTYnkxb09YZzBkbU5rVkZSaE0wRRAB!2m1!1s0x0:0xb0b350462f6165b6!3m1!1s2@1:CAIQACodChtycF9oOnlnd2I0TGFSby1oOXg0dmNkVFRhM0E%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 months ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2026-04-09T23:13:32+00:00"
