          "description": "Dr. Sun was exceptionally rude. He spent 30 seconds with my 3-year-old daughter before dismissing her symptoms. \"There's nothing wrong with her.\" Yet he still sent us for X-rays. The X-ray technician was kind and gentle. Afterward we waited 30 minutes with no explanation of next steps in the exam room\u2014after already being there 90 minutes. When I stepped out briefly to ask about timing so I could manage my daughter\u2019s needs, Dr. Sun threatened not to assist with getting the X-rays read and said, \u201cI\u2019m not holding you against your will. Do whatever you want.\u201d\n\nOn follow-up, he offered no guidance on how to address her symptoms and misrepresented the visit when speaking with my husband, who called for clarification. His dismissive attitude and lack of communication made an already stressful situation much worse. I will never take a child there again.",
